<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes. The call content_len = strlen(content); can read past the bounds of the object if the provided content pointer does not point to a NUL-terminated character array. For example, if a caller passes a buffer char buf[10] filled with 10 bytes and no '\0' terminator (or passes binary data), strlen(content) will scan beyond the 10 bytes seeking a '\0', causing out-of-bounds access and violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
